title.narrative: Percentage of urban citizens satisfied with the quality of infrastructure services

comment.narrative: Pelotas numbers from Sept-2009 posted 81.50% satisfaction.A survey conducted on March-2012 for Pelotas showed 68.8% ofsatisfaction with paving services and public spaces conservation.No specific surveys were carried out by the Project’s closingdate.Information presented in the Borrower’s Independent Assessment demonstrated that objectives related to the improvement ofthe infrastructure services were fully reached.

title.narrative: Percentage of citizens satisfied with quicker and more user-friendly access to client services provided by the municipality

comment.narrative: Pelotas numbers from a survey conducted on March-2012 post 74.80% satisfaction / approval of the public administration.Nospecificsurveys were carried out by the Project’s closing date.

title.narrative: Number of people in rural areas provided with access to Improved Water Sources under the project

comment.narrative: Pelotas numbers.Among the 560 beneficiaries of the Popular Comercial Facility supported by the Project, formality increased from50% to 70%.Pelotas has also implemented a fast business licensing system (alvara expresso).

title.narrative: Number of good practices or innovations replicated from other municipalities

target.value: At least 3 good practice or innovations replicated - Pelotas

comment.narrative: Pelotas numbers.The practices include: (i) Popular commercial facility housing 500 beneficiaries, which was implemented via PPP;(ii) rural producers association, which benefited from Project’s investment in productive infrastructure / packing house; and (iii)Technology Park – a business plan was developed and the Municipality was undergoing final negotiation with partners for itsimplementation.

title.narrative: Reduction in percentage of the density of vehicles in selected avenues benefitted by the project

comment.narrative: Pelotas numbers from 2009 post a reduction of -42%. No specific surveys were carried out by the Project’s closing date.

target.value: Packing House, Commercial Center and Technological Park

comment.narrative: Pelotas numbers. They account for 1 Packing House and 1 Commercial Center.

title.narrative: Number of properties cadastred in automated information systems

comment.narrative: Pelotas numbers. They refer both to the GIS and to land property database (57,000).

title.narrative: Number of municipal projects institutionalizing improved evaluation, social and environmental management processes in the municipalgovernment

comment.narrative: Pelotas numbers. They refer to: (i) the adoption, by the Municipality, of a methodology to supervise works; (ii) theinstitutionalization of the Urban Landscape Catalogue; and (iii) the fact that the PMU, initially created to only deal with theProject management, has been confirmed by the Municipality as a central project development / supervising unit.

title.narrative: Physical progress of urban improvements and environmental recovery as a percentage of target attained: m2 of green areas recovered

actual.value: 1 urban park with 3,700 m2 of green area.

title.narrative: Physical progress of water infrastructure improvements in absolute numbers; number of new piped household water connections that are resulting from the project intervention

target.value: 20 km of water network;600 household connections

actual.value: 20 Km of water supply network; 522 water connections.

title.narrative: Number of beneficiaries of training and/or technical assistance(cluster firms and street vendors, rural producers, innovative firms, and incubated firms)

target.value: 500 - cluster firms and street vendors60 rural producers5 innovative firms10 incubated firms

title.narrative: Percentage of annual work program delivered on time
Volume of Bank Support: Enabling Environment - Microfinance

comment.narrative: The Project hasn’t provided direct USD support to microfinances.However, TA was delivered throughout the implementation ofPelotas project. The Municipal Secretary of Economic Development has developed a microfinance program in partnership with Caixa,Banrisul and Banco do Brasil. By the end of 2012, 3,547 micro entrepreneurs were assisted, with a total USD 7,684,730.00.
To be defined for next mission.

title.narrative: Physical progress of infrastructure improvements in urban transport as a percentage of target attained: roads rehabilitated; roads maintained; substituted, rehabilitated or duplicated bridges

target.value: 55 km of roads rehabilitated;1,200 km of roads maintained; 12 substituted, rehabilitated or duplicated bridges

actual.value: 152 streets paved (81.7 Km); 1200 Km of rural roads maintained; 12 bridges constructed and/or rehabilitated; 20 Km of water supplynetwork; 522 water connections.
